## Plugin Extension Points

```javascript
import { createPlugin } from '{pkg}';

const myPlugin = createPlugin('my-plugin', {
  // Add a new block tag
  tags: {
    'spoiler': {
      attrs: { title: { type: 'string', required: true } },
      content: 'block',
      transform(node, ctx) {
        return { ...node, type: 'details', attrs: { summary: node.attrs.title } };
      },
    },
  },

  // Add a transformer pass
  passes: [
    {
      name:  'resolve-embeds',
      after: 'inline',
      run(ast, ctx) {
        // walk and mutate ast
      },
    },
  ],

  // Custom validator rules
  rules: [
    {
      id: 'no-empty-tip',
      check(node, report) {
        if (node.type === 'callout' && !node.children.length) {
          report.warn(node, 'Callout has no content');
        }
      },
    },
  ],
});

export default myPlugin;
```

<note>
Plugins are registered via `pipeline(source, { plugins: [myPlugin] })` or
through the editor plugin manager at runtime.
</note>

---

## Changelog

<details summary="v8.1.0 — current">

- `transform()` now accepts `mathEngine: 'auto'` (new default); automatically
  falls back from KaTeX to MathJax per-expression rather than per-document
- `validate()` returns `hints` array (previously bundled with warnings)
- New diagnostic codes: V007 (undefined equation label), V008 (duplicate anchor)
- `pipeline()` result now includes `components` map of all registered definitions
- Parser: `<image>` inside `<gallery>` now correctly accepts `caption` attr

</details>

<details summary="v8.0.0">

- **Breaking:** removed all `@directive` block syntax. Use `<Tag>` throughout.
- **Breaking:** `$…$` no longer parsed as math. Use `<m>…</m>`.
- New: `<component>` system with named slots and scoped variables
- New: `<hero>` block with parallax and text-animation attrs
- New: `<gallery>` with built-in lightbox
- VDom diffing in preview — full re-renders eliminated

</details>
